    <div class="container">
      <div class="panel panel-default">
        <div class="panel-heading">
            <h2>Guide - Commands in Yeoman Workflow</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="panel-body">
            <h3>Development</h3>
            <h4>Overview</h4>
            <p>There are only four commands that you need to know about:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><code>grunt build</code> for building the project.</li>
                <li><code>grunt serve</code> for starting the server.</li>
                <li><code>grunt jshint</code> for linting syntax errors in JavaScript.</li>
                <li><code>bower install --save &lt;dependency_name&gt;</code> for installing new dependencies.</li>
            </ul>
            <h4>Building</h4>
            <p>We use</p>
            <pre>grunt build</pre>
            <p>to build the project.</p>
            <p>This will do many things, including wiring dependencies to HTML files, compiling SCSS to CSS, minimizing CSS and uglifying JavaScript, modifying the code to support older browsers, etc.</p>
            <p>You do not have to dig into details about how the project is built when doing this assignment.</p>
            <h4>Serving</h4>
            <p>In development, we use</p>
            <pre>grunt serve</pre>
            <p>to start the server.</p>
            <p>This will automatically open a new tab in your browser and show <code>localhost:9000</code>. It will also watch files, check the syntax errors in the code, and automatically reload the page in the browser. </p>
            <h4>Linting</h4>
            <p>To check obvious syntax errors with JSHint, we use</p>
            <pre>grunt jshint</pre>
            <p>This will give you something similar to </p>
            <img src="../assignment_spec_images/JSHint.png" class="img-responsive"></img>

            <h4>Adding Dependencies</h4>
            <p>You will use <code>bower</code> to add dependencies to the project: </p>
            <pre>bower install --save &lt;dependency_name&gt;</pre>
            <p>For example, if you are installing <code>underscore</code>, issue at the root of the project:</p>
            <pre>bower install --save underscore</pre>
            <p>Note that <code>--save</code> will write the dependency to <code>bower.json</code>.</p>
            <p>You don't use <code>npm</code> to add dependencies, for it's used for pulling dependencies for the server, and you are only developing the front-end. </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

